thread.title: Trump talks money while campaigning in South Carolina
thread.title_full: Trump talks money while campaigning in South Carolina

author: Editor - Political News
title: Trump talks money while campaigning in South Carolina
text:
ANDERSON, S.C. (AP) — Republican presidential front-runner Donald Trump says that money won’t make the difference for candidates this election cycle. 
Trump spoke Monday evening in front of an enthusiastic crowd of thousands at the Civic Center of Anderson, South Carolina. 
It was his latest visit to the early-voting state. 
Financial disclosure reports released last week show that the billionaire has attracted tens of thousands of small-dollar contributions. 
He has also spawned several super PACs that can raise unlimited funds. 
But Trump says that he doesn’t think that bringing in huge contributions will help rivals like former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush prevail. 
He says that if candidates don’t resonate with voters, all the money in the world won’t help. Politics Government
